                            <comment id="11823" author="leanne" created="Thu, 31 Aug 2017 17:05:04 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;To fix, use the following for the date in Perfect-SMTP, SMTP.swift file:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add an import:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;import Foundation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add within the String extension:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  /// get RFC 5322-compliant date for email&lt;br/&gt;
  public static var rfc5322Date: String &lt;/p&gt;
{
    let dateFormatter = DateFormatter()
    dateFormatter.locale = Locale.current
    dateFormatter.dateFormat = &quot;EEE, dd MMM yyyy HH:mm:ss Z&quot;
    let compliantDate = dateFormatter.string(from: Date())
    
    return compliantDate
  }

&lt;p&gt;Replace:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    // print a timestamp to the email&lt;br/&gt;
    var timestamp = time(nil)&lt;br/&gt;
    let now = String(cString: asctime(localtime(&amp;amp;timestamp))!)&lt;br/&gt;
    self.body = &quot;Date: &amp;#40;now)&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    self.body = &quot;Date: &amp;#40;String.rfc5322Date)\r\n&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11824" author="rocky" created="Thu, 31 Aug 2017 22:45:38 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Perfect-SMTP 1.1.4 fixed as your suggestion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, please note that it is not the only reason of spam. If found anything more solutions, please also let me know.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Warm,&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rocky.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11839" author="leanne" created="Thu, 14 Sep 2017 14:07:34 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I found an error in the fix code, Rockford: line 322 of SMTP.swift is missing a backslash.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Currently:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;self.body = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Date: (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;.rfc5322Date)\r\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
so, date appears in the header as:&lt;br/&gt;
Date: (String.rfc5322Date)&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Should be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;self.body = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Date: \(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;.rfc5322Date)\r\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
so, date appears in the header as:&lt;br/&gt;
Date: Thu, 14 Sep 2017 12:43:08 -0500&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
Sorry for the extra work! I apparently had a typo in my example code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
